## Why This Is Asked
Tests the ability to design ephemeral, per-invocation identity management in a multi-region edge computing environment with hardware-backed security, focusing on latency optimization, policy enforcement, and cryptographic agility.

## Key Concepts
- Ephemeral per-invocation identities with SPIFFE IDs
- Hardware-backed root of trust and regional attestation
- Central KCA architecture with short-lived certificates (300s TTL)
- Cross-region trust anchor distribution and management
- Post-quantum cryptography fallback mechanisms
- Per-tenant policy binding and enforcement
- Real-time certificate revocation and auditing
- Cold-start latency optimization and reattestation testing

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo-code: Attestation flow sketch
function issueEdgeCert(region, tenant, invocationId) {
  const root = loadHardwareRoot(region);
  const attestation = regionalBootstrap(root, {
    tenantId: tenant,
    invocationId: invocationId,
    scope: 'edge-func'
  });

  const csr = generateCSR({
    spiffeId: `spiffe://example.com/edge/${tenant}/${invocationId}`,
    ttl: 300,
    extensions: {
      'edge-func': true,
      'region': region,
      'tenant': tenant
    }
  });

  return centralKCA.issue(csr, attestation);
}
```

## Why This Is Asked
